@DATABASE "Mission Jupiter"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - M - Mission Jupiter"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - M
                   ====================================

                              Mission Jupiter
                              ===============



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(60468,0)"}          60468,0
@{"Infinite Fuel " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(57806,0)"}          57806,0
@{"Infinite Ammo " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58322,0)"}          58322,0
@{"Immunity      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58534,201)"}          58534,201
@{"No Enemies    " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(50964,201)"}          50964,201
@{"Move anywhere " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(57774,189)"}          57774,189
@{"No Alien Fire " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58329,201)"}          58329,201
@{"Mega Laser    " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58312,0) ZXAMPoke(58254,0)"}          58312,0:58254,0
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(60266,255)"}          60266,255
@{"Autofire      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58254,0)"}          58254,0
@{"Immune Aliens!" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58659,201)"}          58659,201


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).


                         I don't know if the "No Enemies" POKE works or not,
                         but they all still seem to be there at the early
                         stages of the game. I also don't know what the 
                         "Move Anywhere" POKE does.

                         Rastan
@endnode
